ony-bettenhausen.html Tony Bettenhausen] at the [[Motorsports Hall of Fame of America]]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110724044601/http://www.thegreatest33.com/default.aspx#selecteddrivers?s=tony_bettenhausen The Greatest 33]\n\n{{USAC Drivers' Champions}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bettenhausen, Tony}}\n[[Category:1916 births]]\n[[Category:1961 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American racing drivers]]\n[[Category:Champ Car champions]]\n[[Category:Champ Car drivers]]\n[[Category:Indianapolis 500 drivers]]\n[[Category:International Motorsports Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:People from Tinley Park, Illinois]]\n[[Category:Racing drivers from Illinois]]\n[[Category:Racing drivers killed while racing]]\n[[Category:Sports deaths in Indiana]]\n[[Category:AAA Championship Car drivers]]\n[[Category:World Sportscar Championship drivers]]\n[[Category:Bettenhausen family]]\n", "name_user": "SincerelySteve", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tony_Bettenhausen"}
{"title_page": "Ashland Community Hospital (Oregon)", "text_new": "{{Infobox hospital\n| Image      = Ashland (oregon) community hospital.jpg\n| Image_size = 300px\n| Caption= Hospital entrance\n| Org/Group  = Asante\n| Region     = [[Ashland, Oregon|Ashland]]\n| State      = Oregon\n| Country    = United States\n| HealthCare = Private, [[Non-profit organization|non-profit]]\n| Type       = General medical and surgical\n| Emergency  = IV\n| Beds       = 49\n| Founded    = 1907\n| Website    = http://www.ashlandhospital.org/\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n}}\n\n'''Asante Ashland Community Hospital''' is a hospital in [[Ashland, Oregon|Ashland]], [[Oregon]], [[United States]]. Founded in 1907, it is owned by Asante. In 2012, it explored an affiliation with [[Dignity Health]],<ref>{{cite news|agency=The Associated Press|title=Ashland Community hospital loses $2.5 million in fiscal year, will try to join San Francisco's Dignity Health|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/pacific-northwest-news/index.ssf/2012/08/ashland_community_hospital_los.html|accessdate=29 August 2012|publisher=OregonLive.com|date=August 27, 2012}}</ref> with the latter stopping negotiations in October 2012 over some resistance to the plan.<ref>{{Cite news|agency=The Associated Press|title=Worries over abortion, assisted suicide scuttle takeover of Ashland hospital|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/pacific-northwest-news/index.ssf/2012/10/worries_over_abortion_assisted.html#incart_more_business|accessdate=30 October 2012|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=October 30, 2012}}</ref> On November 15, 2012, Ashland Community Hospital chose to partner with [https://www.asante.org/ Asante], the owner of Three Rivers Medical Center and Rogue Regional Medical Center, to build a stronger financial base for the hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ashland Community Hospital to Partner with Asante |url=http://www.asante.org/about-us/news-media/2012/ashland-community-hospital-to-partner-with-asante/ |publisher=Asante |access-date=2012-11-24 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Ashland's city council approved the transfer to Asante in June 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|agency=The Associated Press|title=Ashland City Council approves takeover of hospital by Asante|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/pacific-northwest-news/index.ssf/2013/06/ashland_city_council_approves.html#incart_more_business|access-date=6 June 2013|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=June 5, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe hospital has 49&nbsp;beds for [[Patient#Outpatients and inpatients|inpatients]], a diagnostic and surgery center with imaging equipment, a laboratory, and equipment for respiratory testing and surgery. Outpatient services cover internal medicine, home health and [[palliative care|hospice]] care, memory care, physical therapy and rehabilitation, school nursing, wound care, and [[hyperbaric medicine]].<ref name=\"Ashland\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.ashlandhospital.org/ |title = Ashland Hospital | accessdate = August 28, 2008 | publisher = Ashland Community Hospital | year = 2008}}</ref>\n\nThe hospital is accredited by the Joint Commission on Accreditation of Health Care Organizations (JCAHO).<ref name = \"US News\">{{Cite web | url = http://health.usnews.com/listings/hospital-directory/oregon/ashland_community_hospital | title = Hospitals Directory: Ashland Community Hospital | accessdate = August 28, 2008 | publisher = U.S. News and World Report | year = 2007| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080830064126/http://health.usnews.com/listings/hospital-directory/oregon/ashland_community_hospital| archivedate= 30 August 2008 <!--DASHBot-->|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of hospitals in Oregon]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Hospitals in Oregon}}\n\n{{coord|42.206277|-122.724951|type:landmark_region:US-OR_source:googlemaps|display=title}} <!-- geocoded \"280 Maple St, Ashland, Oregon\" and adjusted to front door -->\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hospitals in Oregon]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Ashland, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Hospitals established in 1907]]\n[[Category:1907 establishments in Oregon]]\n\n\n{{Oregon-org-stub}}\n{{Oregon-hospital-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox hospital\n| Image      = Ashland (oregon) community hospital.jpg\n| Image_size = 300px\n| Caption= Hospital entrance\n| Org/Group  = Asante\n| Region     = [[Ashland, Oregon|Ashland]]\n| State      = Oregon\n| Country    = United States\n| HealthCare = Private, [[Non-profit organization|non-profit]]\n| Type       = General medical and surgical\n| Emergency  = IV\n| Beds       = 49\n| Founded    = 1907\n| Website    = http://www.ashlandhospital.org/\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n}}\n\n'''Asante Ashland Community Hospital''' is a hospital in [[Ashland, Oregon|Ashland]], [[Oregon]], [[United States]]. Founded in 1907, it is owned by Asante. In 2012, it explored an affiliation with [[Dignity Health]],<ref>{{cite news|agency=The Associated Press|title=Ashland Community hospital loses $2.5 million in fiscal year, will try to join San Francisco's Dignity Health|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/pacific-northwest-news/index.ssf/2012/08/ashland_community_hospital_los.html|accessdate=29 August 2012|publisher=OregonLive.com|date=August 27, 2012}}</ref> with the latter stopping negotiations in October 2012 over some resistance to the plan.<ref>{{Cite news|agency=The Associated Press|title=Worries over abortion, assisted suicide scuttle takeover of Ashland hospital|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/pacific-northwest-news/index.ssf/2012/10/worries_over_abortion_assisted.html#incart_more_business|accessdate=30 October 2012|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=October 30, 2012}}</ref> On November 15, 2012, Ashland Community Hospital chose to partner with [https://www.asante.org/ Asante], the owner of Three Rivers Medical Center and Rogue Regional Medical Center, to build a stronger financial base for the hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ashland Community Hospital to Partner with Asante |url=http://www.asante.org/about-us/news-media/2012/ashland-community-hospital-to-partner-with-asante/ |publisher=Asante |access-date=2012-11-24 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Ashland's city council approved the transfer to Asante in June 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|agency=The Associated Press|title=Ashland City Council approves takeover of hospital by Asante|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/pacific-northwest-news/index.ssf/2013/06/ashland_city_council_approves.html#incart_more_business|access-date=6 June 2013|newspaper=The Oregonian|date=June 5, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe hospital has 49&nbsp;beds for [[Patient#Outpatients and inpatients|inpatients]], a diagnostic and surgery center with imaging equipment, a laboratory, and equipment for respiratory testing and surgery. Outpatient services cover internal medicine, home health and [[palliative care|hospice]] care, memory care, physical therapy and rehabilitation, school nursing, wound care, and [[hyperbaric medicine]].<ref name=\"Ashland\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.ashlandhospital.org/ |title = Ashland Hospital | accessdate = August 28, 2008 | publisher = Ashland Community Hospital | year = 2008}}</ref>\n\nThe hospital is accredited by the Joint Commission on Accreditation of Health Care Organizations (JCAHO).<ref name = \"US News\">{{Cite web | url = http://health.usnews.com/listings/hospital-directory/oregon/ashland_community_hospital | title = Hospitals Directory: Ashland Community Hospital | accessdate = August 28, 2008 | publisher = U.S. News and World Report | year = 2007| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080830064126/http://health.usnews.com/listings/hospital-directory/oregon/ashland_community_hospital| archivedate= 30 August 2008 <!--DASHBot-->|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of hospitals in Oregon]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Hospitals in Oregon}}\n\n{{coord|42.206277|-122.724951|type:landmark_region:US-OR_s